<br>
Hope that made sense, i only just understood it myself. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvalinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/17/01 4:53:38 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another question on ES arms</span><hr size=1> True it is more versitile when you can cast Breath of Ro or Winged Death, but it is also useful when low or out of mana too.  I have also medded to full while killing a mob with just the ES arms and Root.  I'd say the ES arms are one of the most useful pieces of equipment we have available to us and if you have the opportunity to get a set, go for it.<br>
<br>
Valinn <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uneek11.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neek11</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/17/01 4:55:08 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another question on ES arms</span><hr size=1> /second Valinn<br>
<br>
These have saved my bacon when OOM more times than I'd like to remember.  As long as you can keep a mob rooted/snared it will eventually go down. <p>Neek Neekerbeekers<BR>
Halfling Wanderer of the 54th Leaf<BR>Seekers of Divinity<BR>Rallos Zek
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=deneldor>Deneldor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/17/01 9:29:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Another question on ES arms</span><hr size=1> Thanks guys, for some reason that hadnt even crossed my mind...lol. Those annoying slivers of health that take 2 days to melee away or half a bub of mana to nuke becasue you dont have anything smaller memmed.<br>
<br>
/auction WTB ES vambraces (ECI) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usyldane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>syldane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/20/01 12:48:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another question on ES arms</span><hr size=1> Definitely a great item to have.  I rarely even used the 44th swarm spell because I usually immolated and then used my ES vams to dot the mobs down.  Combine it with the Tunarean symbol's root, and you can have manafree rooting and one dot, with the only mana use going to immolate or Breath of Ro at 52.  This is probably the item I would miss the most if I were to lose it for some reason.  Also, if you are in Healer mode, you can add a dot without costing you any mana.  The caveat being that the cast takes a long time.  You wouldn't want to be tied up casting for twice the time of Drones of Doom while your party members die for lack of a heal. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujarinyasinsemilia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarinya Sinsemilia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/21/01 12:24:21 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.aim.fr/gdl/pics/eq/Jarinya.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another question on ES arms</span><hr size=1> ES arms are a must for ANY soloer druid. I replace them by Vermi arms whenever I'm in a group, but they are great to finish off those nasties you're quadkiting, when they all are about to die and you're oom (/point raptors)<br>
<br>
Before I bought them, I was asking why people find them so great, with a very little dot and the annoying casting time. Now I used them a lot, I understand :) Try them, you'll never get rid of them (although you get some Velious bracers :))<br>
